cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on optimizing user association, packet offloading rates, and bandwidth allocation for IoT services in MEC systems, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with minimizing packet loss probability subject to end-to-end delay requirements, which involves information theory concepts such as channel coding and error correction. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an algorithm to solve the nonconvex optimization problem, which involves system modeling and control. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the deployment of processor-sharing servers at MEC systems, which involves distributed computing concepts. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers eMBB services with long packets as background services, which may involve multimedia content such as video streaming.
